The point is that a pilot is expected to achieve a kind of mind-melded harmony with the robot to operate it, and because the resulting "neural load" is too onerous for just one person, he has to work with a partner and achieve "drift" with them too, intermeshing with the other's consciousness. So we get many internal glimpses of each jaeger pilot's mental world, and Inception-lite delving, which slows and hobbles the action-enjoyment without deepening it.
